embarrassingly inept writing although vestal establishes his credibility as a researcher , it is not enough to research well ; one must also be a writer , and vestal 's embarrassing attempts to mimic bridger 's speech is a travesty . from inane , trite cliches to ungrammatical and unmusical diction , it is clear that vestal needed a much stronger editor . recommended only for those who can ignore the non-standard grammar and abyssmal writing or who are interested only in the research